b79ba618-fa6e-4144-bab3-14d169580ab6.48a70713-2659-4e68-904d-2aac13faf452.description=
Gets the host power state, using Proliant iLO.

Inputs\:
    host - The target Proliant iLO processor.
    username - The iLO user name.
    password - The iLO password associated with the  input value.
    port - The SSL port.
Default value\: 443

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. An empty string, if the operation completed successfully. Otherwise, it contains a message indicating failure reason.

Responses\:
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
    power off - The host power is off.
    power on - The host power is on.
b79ba618-fa6e-4144-bab3-14d169580ab6.65b8d12c-9a13-44c6-8862-3adeb223b82a.description=
Checks if a number or word is equal to another number or word. Word comparison is case-sensitive in alphabetical order.

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.

Returns\:
value1 \=\= value2

Responses\:
success - The boolean operation was evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.
b79ba618-fa6e-4144-bab3-14d169580ab6.73239a6c-c711-42fb-92e7-27e986e9641a.description=
This operation waits for the number of seconds specified in the "seconds" input.

Inputs\:
    seconds - The number of seconds to wait.

Results\:
    resultString – This is the primary output. It contains the "completed sleep" message if the operation completed successfully and an error message otherwise. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
b79ba618-fa6e-4144-bab3-14d169580ab6.73750db7-f16b-484e-b9d0-2348aeedff5d.description=
This operation adds a flow variable to the local context. The variable is available in the current flow and its child flows.

Inputs\:
    keyName - The name of the flow variable to add.
    myValue - The value to assign to the flow variable.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value of "myValue" input field.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.

Note\:
   If a flow variable with the same name already exists, its value will be overwritten.
